rComments: Lectures can feel a bit spastic at times, but he is very enthusiastic about the material and knows his stuff. Open to student feedback and cares that they are doing well. Accommodating for students extenuating circumstances (yay for being bedridden for 2 weeks). Tests are tough but fair.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Caring', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Great professor. WIll re-explain concepts in class if asked and his tests largely reflect the material taught in class. Very fair and approachable. Lectures were a bit disorganized.

Great lecturer, fair tester, but a bit picky when it comes to what he considers an "acceptable" answer. He'll always tell you why something is wrong if you do lose marks on a test, which is nice. His answers are always very reasonable. He's a bit disorganized, in the sense that he'll reply to emails maybe 1 out of 5 times. Overall decent prof.
